content.text:
Let me analyze the images and break this down systematically:

Target Image Analysis:
- Structure consists of 2 blocks
- Bottom layer: Green rectangular block (horizontal orientation)
- Top layer: Orange cylindrical block with an orange triangular top piece
- Total layers: 2
- Spatial arrangement: Orange cylindrical block is vertically centered on the green rectangular block

Block Dictionary Selection:
- Green Block: Index 2 (horizontal rectangular green block)
- Orange Cylindrical Block: Index 5 (vertical orange cylinder)
- Orange Triangular Top: Index 11 (small orange triangular block)

Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 2
    Step2: Move block with index 5 (centered on block 2)
    Step3: Move block with index 11 (on top of block 5)
}

The assembly follows a bottom-up approach, starting with the green base block, then placing the orange cylindrical block centered on it, and finally adding the orange triangular top piece to complete the structure exactly as shown in the main target image.
